    <weatherForecast/>
    <avalancheActivity>
      <highlights>The weather will be partly cloudy over a wide area. &lt;br/> Warming.</highlights>
      <comment>The avalanche prone locations for dry avalanches are to be found on steep shady slopes above approximately 2500 m. &lt;br/> As a consequence of warming during the day and the solar radiation, the likelihood of wet avalanches being released will increase in particular on steep shady slopes below approximately 2500 m. &lt;br/> Medium-sized avalanches are possible.</comment>
    </avalancheActivity>
    <snowpackStructure>
      <comment>The surface of the snowpack will already soften in the late morning. &lt;br/> Above approximately 2400 m snow fell in the last few days in some regions. &lt;br/> As a consequence of wind, mostly shallow wind slabs formed in high Alpine regions. &lt;br/> Steep shady slopes above approximately 2500 m: Faceted weak layers exist in the bottom section of the old snowpack. &lt;br/> Below approximately 2000 m from a snow sport perspective, in most cases insufficient snow is lying.</comment>
    </snowpackStructure>
